Headquarters Regions: San Francisco Bay Area, West Coast, Western US
Full Description: BiosPacific is a supplier of bulk Antibodies and Antigens for Immunoassay Development. BiosPacific, Inc. was founded in 1989 as a supplier of immunological reagents to the commercial diagnostic industry. Our strength over the years has been to consistently meet the demands of this dynamic industry and our diverse customer base. Twenty-five years later we remain committed to supporting this ever changing marketplace and so continue to develop new products that will further the advancement of diagnostic technology. We offer more than 2,000 products including highly purified monoclonal and polyclonal antibodies, native and recombinant proteins as well as a wide range of conjugates. Although our focus is in the areas of cardiac markers, cancer markers, drugs of abuse, thyroid, infectious disease and steroids we do offer many reagents outside of these areas. As we look to the future our goal is to continually develop new reagents that meet market demand and broaden our already diverse portfolio of biological reagents. We are dedicated to providing materials of only the highest quality and are made in accordance with the stringent standards of the highly regulated environment in which we operate. BiosPacific is honored to continue to be the exclusive US distributor of Medix Biochemica monoclonal antibodies (MedixMab's). As a manufacturer of world class reagents, their ISO certified manufacturing facility is state of the art and has the capability of meeting even the most stringent regulatory demands as well as the capacity to produce industrial scale quantities of all their monoclonal antibodies. They can also provide contract manufacturing services for the in vitro scale-up of monoclonal antibodies to our diagnostic customers. We here at BiosPacific take pride in our commitment to personal service. We strive not just to meet but exceed the expectations of our customers. Our highly skilled staff is always available to provide immediate customer support and technical service. We look forward to the opportunity to serve you!
Industry Groups: Biotechnology, Health Care, Science and Engineering

Full Description: ExampleMotion.com is a file sharing website for legal professionals.  You can search for documents without creating an account. Go to the examplemotion.com search page and start with keywords, or by jurisdiction and type of law. Then filter your results by stage of the proceedings, and by the type of document you are seeking. Finally, check if your document type is further subdivided by a more specific type of document. All of these filters are optional, and you can browse the entire examplemotion.com database, or use these filters to intuitively find the document you are looking for. Once you find a document that has a fitting description, see a preview of the document to make sure it is exactly what you want. After finding your example motion, add it to your cart and check out. Finding an example motion to assist with what you are writing will take less time than it did to read this paragraph! As a legal practitioner, you likely possess many, many documents written for past cases that lay dormant on your computer. ExampleMotion.com is the opportunity to give those documents new life. Simply delete any information from the document that is private or confidential, and use the Upload tab to describe the document, and upload it to the ExampleMotion.com database. In order to promote the objective of this site to promote the free flow of legal ideas and save time for our fellow lawyers, we suggest setting a nominal price for the document of $10.00 to $50.00. Each annual quarter you will receive a check from ExampleMotion.com for half of the sales price of all the documents sold that you uploaded. The other half goes to maintaining and developing the site. Quality control is important to us at ExampleMotion, therefore we have a ratings system and comments section connected to each document. If you have an opinion about the quality of a document that you have purchased, we encourage you to rate and post comments about the brief on our comments board. That way, in addition to the significant internal efforts conducted at ExampleMotion.com to ensure quality control, you, our users, will also be an invaluable resource to make sure that only the most quality briefs are exchanged on our site. Unfortunately, ExampleMotion.com has not yet compiled legal briefs for every aspect of every type of litigation. Therefore we have a Document Requests section where you can request a brief on a specific topic from other ExampleMotion.com users, and converse with potential authors via our pricing and message boards to make sure you get what you want, at a price you can afford. When users post replies to document requests that you have written, you will be informed via email, and can purchase their document if you choose.
Founders: Daniel O'Shea, Dennis Balsamo, Valerio Romano

Description: TherVoyant, Inc. creates comprehensive software and hardware solutions.
Headquarters Regions: Great Lakes, Midwestern US
Full Description: TherVoyant is a scientific software application development company based in Madison, Wisconsin.   Our expert team consists of business leaders, neurosurgeons, scientists and developers with a strong expertise in MRI imaging and neurosurgery. TherVoyant is one of the first companies to develop manufacturer agnostic, real-time imaging software with scanning capabilities that can be customized for each interventional application. TherVoyant has recognized key barriers that have constrained the clinical adoption of MRI-guided procedures. Currently, device companies rely on MRI manufacturers to implement the imaging features and software interfaces needed to guide the MRI-compatible devices. However, the manufacturers typically take years to implement new features. For low-prevalence conditions, the features may never be placed into the standard software release. Using the Apps-based approach, TherVoyant can implement a workflow for a new procedure within a few weeks. TherVoyant’s flagship product, GuideRT, is a technology platform that provides an Apps-based workflow interface to interactively guide surgical procedures with immediate feedback using Real-Time MRI in the areas of neurosurgery, oncology procedures and new drug therapies. With GuideRT, surgeons and healthcare providers can significantly improve surgical procedures,  reduce surgical time and improve the lives of their patients.
